          %h3 Isaiah
          %p I still remember the first thing I hammered together; I found some scrap wood and some old nails and made something that vaugly resembled an airplane. It wasn't a great work, but it was a start. Over the years I helped my dad (whether or not I wanted to) with various projects. Eventually it got to the point where I was making things to put in my own home.
          %p For my main source of income I'm a Senior Web Developer for <a href="http://singlebrook.com">Singlebrook</a>. My affinity for computers and programming lended itself well to working with the CNC machine I purchased in early 2016. I also enjoy sketching and drawing and have been able to use the CNC to bring some of my door hanger designs to life.
